HEADWORD: Forel
<hw>For"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>forel</ets>case, sheath, OF. <ets>forel</ets>, <ets>fourel</ets>,
F. <ets>fourreau</ets>, LL. <ets>forellus</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>forre</ets>, <ets>fuerre</ets>, sheath, case, of German origin; cf.
OHG. <ets>fuotar</ets>, akin to Goth. <ets>f⟦omac⟧dr</ets>; prob. not
the same word as E. <ets>fodder</ets> food. Cf. <er>Fur</er>,
<er>Fodder</er> food.]</ety> <def>A kind of parchment for book covers.
See <er>Forrill</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
